TY  - JOUR
AU  - Finkelstein, Amy
T1  - E-ztax: Tax Salience and Tax Rates*
PY  - 2009
Y1  - 2009/08/01
DO  - 10.1162/qjec.2009.124.3.969
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 124
IS  - 3
SP  - 969
EP  - 1010
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper examines whether the salience of a tax system affects equilibrium tax rates. I analyze how tolls change after toll facilities adopt electronic toll collection (ETC); drivers are substantially less aware of tolls paid electronically. I estimate that, in steady state, tolls are 20 to 40 percent higher than they would have been without ETC. Consistent with a salience-based explanation for this toll increase, I find that under ETC, driving becomes less elastic with respect to the toll and toll setting becomes less sensitive to the electoral calendar. Alternative explanations appear unlikely to be able to explain the findings.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/qjec.2009.124.3.969
ER  - 



